The paper focuses on the problem of task-motion planning in mobile robots, which is a core topic in robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach integrates reinforcement learning (RL) to improve the robustness of the planning process, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of model-free RL, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The approach is designed to handle dynamic and uncertain domains, which is a key challenge in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper evaluates the approach on a mobile service robot, which is a common application of robotics and machine learning (cs.MA).
